name: Academy at Tolaria West
text: At the beginning of your end step, if you have no cards in hand, draw seven cards.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, discard your hand.

name: Akroma's Vengeance
text: Destroy all artifacts, creatures, and enchantments.\nCycling {3} ({3}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
flavor: Ixidor had only to imagine their ruin and Akroma made it so.

name: The Æther Flues
text: When you planeswalk to The Æther Flues or at the beginning of your upkeep, you may sacrifice a creature. If you do, reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a creature card, put that card onto the battlefield, then shuffle all other cards revealed this way into your library.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, you may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield.

name: Congregate
text: Target player gains 2 life for each creature on the battlefield.
flavor: "In the gathering there is strength for all who founder, renewal for all who languish, love for all who sing."\n—Song of All, canto 642

name: Agyrem
text: Whenever a white creature dies, return it to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step.\nWhenever a nonwhite creature dies, return it to its owner's hand at the beginning of the next end step.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, creatures can't attack you until a player planeswalks.

name: Kor Sanctifiers
text: Kicker {W} (You may pay an additional {W} as you cast this spell.)\nWhen Kor Sanctifiers enters the battlefield, if it was kicked, destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: "Why keep such trinkets? They only add weight to your travels."

name: Bant
text: All creatures have exalted. (Whenever a creature attacks alone, it gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each instance of exalted among permanents its controller controls.)\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put a divinity counter on target green, white, or blue creature. That creature has indestructible for as long as it has a divinity counter on it.

name: Oblivion Ring
text: When Oblivion Ring enters the battlefield, exile another target nonland permanent.\nWhen Oblivion Ring leaves the battlefield, return the exiled card to the battlefield under its owner's control.

name: Cliffside Market
text: When you planeswalk to Cliffside Market or at the beginning of your upkeep, you may exchange life totals with target player.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, exchange control of two target permanents that share a card type.

name: Orim's Thunder
text: Kicker {R} (You may pay an additional {R} as you cast this spell.)\nDestroy target artifact or enchantment. If Orim's Thunder was kicked, it deals damage equal to that permanent's converted mana cost to target creature.

name: The Dark Barony
text: Whenever a nonblack card is put into a player's graveyard from anywhere, that player loses 1 life.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, each opponent discards a card.

name: Prison Term
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature can't attack or block, and its activated abilities can't be activated.\nWhenever a creature enters the battlefield under an opponent's control, you may attach Prison Term to that creature.

name: Eloren Wilds
text: Whenever a player taps a permanent for mana, that player adds one mana to his or her mana pool of any type that permanent produced.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, target player can't cast spells until a player planeswalks.

name: Soul Warden
text: Whenever another creature enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life.
flavor: "One does not question the size or shape of the grains of sand in an hourglass. Nor do I question the temperament of the souls under my guidance."

name: The Eon Fog
text: Players skip their untap steps.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, untap all permanents you control.

name: Broodstar
text: Affinity for artifacts (This spell costs {1} less to cast for each artifact you control.)\nFlying\nBroodstar's power and toughness are each equal to the number of artifacts you control.

name: Feeding Grounds
text: Red spells cost {1} less to cast.\nGreen spells cost {1} less to cast.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put X +1/+1 counters on target creature, where X is that creature's converted mana cost.

name: Fabricate
text: Search your library for an artifact card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: "The secret to invention is to see something in your mind, then find where it hides in the world."

name: Fields of Summer
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, that player may gain 2 life.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, you may gain 10 life.

name: Keep Watch
text: Draw a card for each attacking creature.
flavor: "I see their moral dilemmas. I see their raw courage. I see their self-sacrifice. I see our victory."

name: The Fourth Sphere
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice a nonblack creature.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield.

name: Master of Etherium
text: Master of Etherium's power and toughness are each equal to the number of artifacts you control.\nOther artifact creatures you control get +1/+1.
flavor: "Only a mind unfettered with the concerns of the flesh can see the world as it truly is."

name: Glimmervoid Basin
text: Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery spell with a single target, he or she copies that spell for each other spell, permanent, card not on the battlefield, and/or player the spell could target. Each copy targets a different one of them.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, choose target creature. Each player except that creature's controller puts a token that's a copy of that creature onto the battlefield.

name: Qumulox
text: Affinity for artifacts (This spell costs {1} less to cast for each artifact you control.)\nFlying
flavor: Even the clouds bend themselves to Memnarch's will, eager to swallow those who oppose him.

name: Goldmeadow
text: Whenever a land enters the battlefield, that land's controller puts three 0/1 white Goat creature tokens onto the battlefield.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put a 0/1 white Goat creature token onto the battlefield.

name: Sarcomite Myr
text: {2}: Sarcomite Myr gains flying until end of turn.\n{2}, Sacrifice Sarcomite Myr: Draw a card.
flavor: "A horrible sight, yes, but the sounds . . . Its twanging tendons and grinding gears are almost musical."\n—Brudiclad, Telchor engineer

name: The Great Forest
text: Each creature assigns combat damage equal to its toughness rather than its power.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, creatures you control get +0/+2 and gain trample until end of turn.

name: Thirst for Knowledge
text: Draw three cards. Then discard two cards unless you discard an artifact card.
flavor: Lymph, the fluid essence of blinkmoths, is prized by wizards for the rush of intellect it provides.

name: Grixis
text: Blue, black, and/or red creature cards in your graveyard have unearth. The unearth cost is equal to the card's mana cost. (Pay the card's mana cost: Return it to the battlefield. The creature gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put target creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.

name: Vedalken Engineer
text: {T}: Add two mana of any one color to your mana pool. Spend this mana only to cast artifact spells or activate abilities of artifacts.
flavor: Art is unknown to the vedalken—for them, all creations must serve a purpose.

name: The Hippodrome
text: All creatures get -5/-0.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, you may destroy target creature if its power is 0 or less.

name: Whiplash Trap
text: If an opponent had two or more creatures enter the battlefield under his or her control this turn, you may pay {U} rather than pay Whiplash Trap's mana cost.\nReturn two target creatures to their owners' hands.

name: Immersturm
text: Whenever a creature enters the battlefield, that creature's controller may have it deal damage equal to its power to target creature or player of his or her choice.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, exile target creature, then return it to the battlefield under its owner's control.

name: Ascendant Evincar
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nOther black creatures get +1/+1.\nNonblack creatures get -1/-1.
flavor: His soul snared by an angel's curse, Crovax twisted heroism into its purest shadow.

name: Isle of Vesuva
text: Whenever a nontoken creature enters the battlefield, its controller puts a token onto the battlefield that's a copy of that creature.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, destroy target creature and all other creatures with the same name as that creature.

name: Beacon of Unrest
text: Put target artifact or creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. Shuffle Beacon of Unrest into its owner's library.
flavor: A vertical scream pierces the night air and echoes doom through the clouds.

name: Izzet Steam Maze
text: Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery spell, that player copies it. The player may choose new targets for the copy.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, instant and sorcery spells you cast this turn cost {3} less to cast.

name: Beseech the Queen
text: ({2/B} can be paid with any two mana or with {B}. This card's converted mana cost is 6.)\nSearch your library for a card with converted mana cost less than or equal to the number of lands you control, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Those who hear her go mad with inspiration.

name: Krosa
text: All creatures get +2/+2.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, you may add {W}{U}{B}{R}{G} to your mana pool.

name: Cadaverous Knight
text: Flanking (Whenever a creature without flanking blocks this creature, the blocking creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.)\n{1}{B}{B}: Regenerate Cadaverous Knight.
flavor: Grieve for the soul in death dishonored.\n—Shadow Guild saying

name: Lethe Lake
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, put the top ten cards of your library into your graveyard.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, target player puts the top ten cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard.

name: Consume Spirit
text: Spend only black mana on X.\nConsume Spirit deals X damage to target creature or player and you gain X life.

name: Llanowar
text: All creatures have "{T}: Add {G}{G} to your mana pool."\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, untap all creatures you control.

name: Corpse Harvester
text: {1}{B}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature: Search your library for a Zombie card and a Swamp card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then shuffle your library.

name: The Maelstrom
text: When you planeswalk to The Maelstrom or at the beginning of your upkeep, you may reveal the top card of your library. If it's a permanent card, you may put it onto the battlefield. If you revealed a card but didn't put it onto the battlefield, put it on the bottom of your library.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, return target permanent card from your graveyard to the battlefield.

name: Cruel Revival
text: Destroy target non-Zombie creature. It can't be regenerated. Return up to one target Zombie card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Few Cabal fighters fear death. They fear what follows it.

name: Minamo
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, that player may draw a card. \nWhenever you roll CHAOS, each player may return a blue card from his or her graveyard to his or her hand.

name: Dark Ritual
text: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: "If there is such a thing as too much power, I have not discovered it."\n—Volrath

name: Murasa
text: Whenever a nontoken creature enters the battlefield, its controller may search his or her library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle his or her library.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, target land becomes a 4/4 creature that's still a land.

name: Death Baron
text: Skeleton creatures you control and other Zombie creatures you control get +1/+1 and have deathtouch.
flavor: For the necromancer barons, killing and recruitment are one and the same.

name: Naar Isle
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, put a flame counter on Naar Isle, then Naar Isle deals damage to you equal to the number of flame counters on it.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, Naar Isle deals 3 damage to target player.

name: Dregscape Zombie
text: Unearth {B} ({B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)
flavor: The undead of Grixis are fueled by their hatred of the living.

name: Naya
text: You may play any number of lands on each of your turns.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, target red, green, or white creature you control gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each land you control.

name: Festering Goblin
text: When Festering Goblin dies, target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: In life, it was a fetid, disease-ridden thing. In death, not much changed.

name: Otaria
text: Instant and sorcery cards in graveyards have flashback. The flashback cost is equal to the card's mana cost. (Its owner may cast the card from his or her graveyard for its mana cost. Then he or she exiles it.)\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, take an extra turn after this one.

name: Grave Pact
text: Whenever a creature you control dies, each other player sacrifices a creature.
flavor: "The bonds of loyalty can tie one to the grave."\n—Crovax, ascendant evincar

name: Panopticon
text: When you planeswalk to Panopticon, draw a card.\nAt the beginning of your draw step, draw an additional card.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, draw a card.

name: Gravedigger
text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Oddly, no one questioned the Cabal's wisdom in hiring a zombie to work at the cemetery.

name: Pools of Becoming
text: At the beginning of your end step, put the cards in your hand on the bottom of your library in any order, then draw that many cards.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, reveal the top three cards of your planar deck. Each of the revealed cards' CHAOS abilities triggers. Then put the revealed cards on the bottom of your planar deck in any order.

name: Helldozer
text: {B}{B}{B}, {T}: Destroy target land. If that land was nonbasic, untap Helldozer.
flavor: Sometimes you go to hell, and sometimes hell comes to you.

name: Raven's Run
text: All creatures have wither. (They deal damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters.)\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put a -1/-1 counter on target creature, two -1/-1 counters on another target creature, and three -1/-1 counters on a third target creature.

name: Hideous End
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. Its controller loses 2 life.
flavor: "A little dark magic won't stop me. The worse the curse, the better the prize."\n—Radavi, Joraga relic hunter, last words

name: Sanctum of Serra
text: When you planeswalk away from Sanctum of Serra, destroy all nonland permanents.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, you may have your life total become 20.

name: Incremental Blight
text: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature, two -1/-1 counters on another target creature, and three -1/-1 counters on a third target creature.
flavor: Shadowmoor's main crops are rot, slime, and despair.

name: Sea of Sand
text:
Players reveal each card they draw.
Whenever a player draws a land card, that player gains 3 life.
Whenever a player draws a nonland card, that player loses 3 life.
Whenever you roll CHAOS, put target permanent on top of its owner's library.

name: Innocent Blood
text: Each player sacrifices a creature.
flavor: Zombies mourn for the living and celebrate those who will soon be given the gift of death.

name: Shiv
text: All creatures have "{R}: This creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn."\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, put a 5/5 red Dragon creature token with flying onto the battlefield.

name: Nefashu
text: Whenever Nefashu attacks, up to five target creatures each get -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: Where the nefashu pass, blood rolls like a silk carpet.

name: Skybreen
text: Players play with the top card of their libraries revealed.\nSpells that share a card type with the top card of a library can't be cast.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, target player loses life equal to the number of cards in his or her hand.

name: Noxious Ghoul
text: Whenever Noxious Ghoul or another Zombie enters the battlefield, all non-Zombie creatures get -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: Plague and death wrapped in one convenient package.

name: Sokenzan
text: All creatures get +1/+1 and have haste.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, untap all creatures that attacked this turn. After this main phase, there is an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase.

name: Phyrexian Arena
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor: A drop of humanity for a sea of power.

name: Stronghold Furnace
text: If a source would deal damage to a creature or player, it deals double that damage to that creature or player instead.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, Stronghold Furnace deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Phyrexian Ghoul
text: Sacrifice a creature: Phyrexian Ghoul gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: Phyrexia wastes nothing. Its food chain is a spiraling cycle.

name: Turri Island
text: Creature spells cost {2} less to cast.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, reveal the top three cards of your library. Put all creature cards revealed this way into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.

name: Profane Command
text:
Choose two —
• Target player loses X life. 
• Return target creature card with converted mana cost X or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.
• Target creature gets -X/-X until end of turn.
• Up to X target creatures gain fear until end of turn. (They can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)

name: Undercity Reaches
text: Whenever a creature deals combat damage to a player, its controller may draw a card.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, you have no maximum hand size for the rest of the game.

name: Rotting Rats
text: When Rotting Rats enters the battlefield, each player discards a card.\nUnearth {1}{B} ({1}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

name: Velis Vel
text: Each creature gets +1/+1 for each other creature on the battlefield that shares at least one creature type with it. (For example, if two Elemental Shamans and an Elemental Spirit are on the battlefield, each gets +2/+2.)\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, target creature gains all creature types until end of turn.

name: Shepherd of Rot
text: {T}: Each player loses 1 life for each Zombie on the battlefield.
flavor: "My priests swore loyalty to the Cabal not until death, but beyond it."\n—Cabal Patriarch

name: Tazeem
text: Creatures can't block.\nWhenever you roll CHAOS, draw a card for each land you control.

name: Soulless One
text: Soulless One's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Zombies on the battlefield plus the number of Zombie cards in all graveyards.
flavor: "Surrender your soul to me."

name: Syphon Mind
text: Each other player discards a card. You draw a card for each card discarded this way.
flavor: When tempers run high, it's easy to lose your head.

name: Syphon Soul
text: Syphon Soul deals 2 damage to each other player. You gain life equal to the damage dealt this way.
flavor: As Phage drank their energy, a vague memory of Jeska stirred. Then she lost herself again in the joy of her victims' suffering.

name: Undead Warchief
text: Zombie spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.\nZombie creatures you control get +2/+1.
flavor: It has the strength of seven men. In fact, it used to be seven men.

name: Withered Wretch
text: {1}: Exile target card from a graveyard.
flavor: Once it consecrated the dead. Now it desecrates them.

name: Arc Lightning
text: Arc Lightning deals 3 damage divided as you choose among one, two, or three target creatures and/or players.
flavor: Rainclouds don't last long in Shiv, but that doesn't stop the lightning.

name: Blaze
text: Blaze deals X damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Fire never dies alone.

name: Bogardan Firefiend
text: When Bogardan Firefiend dies, it deals 2 damage to target creature.
flavor: "The next one who tells me to relax and curl up by a fire is dead."\n—Mirri of the Weatherlight

name: Bogardan Rager
text: Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)\nWhen Bogardan Rager enters the battlefield, target creature gets +4/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: In the erupting heart of Bogardan, it's hard to tell hurtling volcanic rocks from pouncing volcanic beasts.

name: Browbeat
text: Any player may have Browbeat deal 5 damage to him or her. If no one does, target player draws three cards.
flavor: "Even the threat of power has power."\n—Jeska, warrior adept

name: Cinder Elemental
text: {X}{R}, {T}, Sacrifice Cinder Elemental: Cinder Elemental deals X damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Their rage can grow to such proportions that they explode in a cloud of fire.

name: Cone of Flame
text: Cone of Flame deals 1 damage to target creature or player, 2 damage to another target creature or player, and 3 damage to a third target creature or player.

name: Flamekin Harbinger
text: When Flamekin Harbinger enters the battlefield, you may search your library for an Elemental card, reveal it, then shuffle your library and put that card on top of it.

name: Flametongue Kavu
text: When Flametongue Kavu enters the battlefield, it deals 4 damage to target creature.
flavor: "For dim-witted, thick-skulled genetic mutants, they have pretty good aim."\n—Sisay, captain of the Weatherlight

name: Furnace of Rath
text: If a source would deal damage to a creature or player, it deals double that damage to that creature or player instead.
flavor: The furnace awaits the next master who would stoke the fires of apocalypse.

name: Goblin Offensive
text: Put X 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: They certainly are.

name: Insurrection
text: Untap all creatures and gain control of them until end of turn. They gain haste until end of turn.
flavor: "Maybe they wanted to be on the winning side for once."\n—Matoc, lavamancer

name: Keldon Champion
text: Haste\nEcho {2}{R}{R} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Keldon Champion enters the battlefield, it deals 3 damage to target player.

name: Menacing Ogre
text: Trample, haste\nWhen Menacing Ogre enters the battlefield, each player secretly chooses a number. Then those numbers are revealed. Each player with the highest number loses that much life. If you are one of those players, put two +1/+1 counters on Menacing Ogre.

name: Pyrotechnics
text: Pyrotechnics deals 4 damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures and/or players.
flavor: "Who says lightning never strikes twice?"\n—Storm shaman

name: Reckless Charge
text: Target creature gets +3/+0 and gains haste until end of turn.\nFlashback {2}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Relentless Assault
text: Untap all creatures that attacked this turn. After this main phase, there is an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase.
flavor: "Mercy? Mercy is for the playground, not the battleground."

name: Rockslide Elemental
text: First strike\nWhenever another creature dies, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Rockslide Elemental.
flavor: On Jund, even the landscape is a deadly hunter. Volcanoes, tar pits, and rock slides seem to prey upon the living.

name: Rolling Thunder
text: Rolling Thunder deals X damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures and/or players.
flavor: "Such rage," thought Vhati, gazing up at the thunderhead from the Predator. "It is Greven's mind manifest."

name: Rorix Bladewing
text: Flying, haste
flavor: In the smoldering ashes of Shiv, a few dragons strive to rebuild their native land. The rest seek any opportunity to restore the broken pride of their race.

name: Smokebraider
text: {T}: Add two mana in any combination of colors to your mana pool. Spend this mana only to cast Elemental spells or activate abilities of Elementals.
flavor: "Be silent and listen to your inner fire. Only then can you walk the Path of Flame."

name: Taurean Mauler
text: Changeling (This card is every creature type at all times.)\nWhenever an opponent casts a spell, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Taurean Mauler.
flavor: The power of a waterfall. The fury of an avalanche. The intellect of a gale-force wind.

name: Beast Hunt
text: Reveal the top three cards of your library. Put all creature cards revealed this way into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.
flavor: "Surely we could tame something besides hurdas and pillarfield oxen!"\n—Sheyda, Ondu gamekeeper

name: Briarhorn
text: Flash\nWhen Briarhorn enters the battlefield, target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.\nEvoke {1}{G} (You may cast this spell for its evoke cost. If you do, it's sacrificed when it enters the battlefield.)

name: Explosive Vegetation
text: Search your library for up to two basic land cards and put them onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Torching Krosa would be pointless. It grows faster than it burns.

name: Fertile Ground
text: Enchant land\nWhenever enchanted land is tapped for mana, its controller adds one mana of any color to his or her mana pool (in addition to the mana the land produces).

name: Fertilid
text: Fertilid enters the battlefield with two +1/+1 counters on it.\n{1}{G}, Remove a +1/+1 counter from Fertilid: Target player searches his or her library for a basic land card and puts it onto the battlefield tapped. Then that player shuffles his or her library.

name: Forgotten Ancient
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Forgotten Ancient.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you may move any number of +1/+1 counters from Forgotten Ancient onto other creatures.
flavor: Its blood is life. Its body is growth.

name: Ivy Elemental
text: Ivy Elemental enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it.
flavor: In the gardens of the centaurs, many travelers have mysteriously vanished while admiring the elaborate topiaries.

name: Living Hive
text: Trample\nWhenever Living Hive deals combat damage to a player, put that many 1/1 green Insect creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: In its center is a single red ant, a queen that regulates the hive's movements.

name: Rampant Growth
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Nature grows solutions to its problems.

name: Search for Tomorrow
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.\nSuspend 2—{G} (Rather than cast this card from your hand, you may pay {G} and exile it with two time counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a time counter. When the last is removed, cast it without paying its mana cost.)

name: Silverglade Elemental
text: When Silverglade Elemental enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a Forest card and put that card onto the battlefield. If you do, shuffle your library.

name: Tornado Elemental
text: When Tornado Elemental enters the battlefield, it deals 6 damage to each creature with flying.\nYou may have Tornado Elemental assign its combat damage as though it weren't blocked.

name: Tribal Unity
text: Creatures of the creature type of your choice get +X/+X until end of turn.
flavor: Kamahl left the violence of his former life behind him, but he still believes in the power of muscle.

name: Verdant Force
text: At the beginning of each upkeep, put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: Left to itself, nature overflows any container, overthrows any restriction, and overreaches any boundary.

name: Boros Swiftblade
text: Double strike
flavor: When the Boros Legion attacks, swiftblades enter the fray first. They pick off the archers and mages, softening the enemy front before the flame-kin and giants go in.

name: Branching Bolt
text: Choose one or both —\n• Branching Bolt deals 3 damage to target creature with flying.\n• Branching Bolt deals 3 damage to target creature without flying.
flavor: "Lightning lives in everything, in living flesh and growing things. It must be set free."\n—Rakka Mar

name: Bull Cerodon
text: Vigilance, haste
flavor: It holds motionless vigil, watching Naya in silence through the screen of the whitecover. When it senses anything amiss, it launches forward with the uncanny sound of torn fog.

name: Captain's Maneuver
text: The next X damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn is dealt to another target creature or player instead.
flavor: Sisay discovered that the mirrored hull of the Weatherlight could be used as a defensive weapon.

name: Cerodon Yearling
text: Vigilance, haste
flavor: The unit of measurement used to chart a cerodon's growth is "persons consumed."

name: Fires of Yavimaya
text: Creatures you control have haste.\nSacrifice Fires of Yavimaya: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Glory of Warfare
text: As long as it's your turn, creatures you control get +2/+0.\nAs long as it's not your turn, creatures you control get +0/+2.
flavor: "Their hopes dashed on our shields! Their victory slashed by our swords!"

name: Hull Breach
text:
Choose one —
• Destroy target artifact.
• Destroy target enchantment.
• Destroy target artifact and target enchantment.
